
---


@startuml

' Main Classes
class Museum {
  - name: String
}

class Location {
  - id: int
  - name: String
  - description: String
  - museum: Museum
}

class Exhibition {
  - id: int
  - name: String
  - startDate: Date
  - endDate: Date
  - location: Location
  - coordinator: Employee
}

class ExhibitionItem {
  - id: int
  - name: String
  - exhibition: Exhibition
}

class Piece {
  - id: int
  - name: String
  - artist: String
  - year: int
}

class Collector {
  - id: int
  - name: String
  - contactInfo: String
}

class Request {
  - id: int
  - status: String
  - exhibitionItem: ExhibitionItem
  - piece: Piece
  - collector: Collector
}

class Employee {
  - id: int
  - name: String
  - role: String
  - coach: Employee
  - mentees: List<Employee>
}

' Relationships
Museum "1" -- "many" Location : contains
Location "1" -- "many" Exhibition : has
Exhibition "1" -- "many" ExhibitionItem : has
ExhibitionItem "1" -- "many" Request : requires
Request "1" -- "1" Piece : requests
Request "1" -- "1" Collector : from
Employee "1" -- "many" Employee : coach <-> mentee
Employee "1" -- "many" Exhibition : coordinates

@enduml

---

### 📌 Explanation of the Model:

- **Museum**: Represents the Louvre Museum as a whole.
- **Location**: A section within the museum (e.g., a floor or wing).
- **Exhibition**: An event that takes place in a location, with a start and end date.
- **ExhibitionItem**: A specific item required for an exhibition (e.g., a painting).
- **Piece**: A physical artwork or item that can be used in an exhibition.
- **Collector**: A person or entity that owns a piece.
- **Request**: A request made to borrow a piece from a collector for an exhibition item.
- **Employee**: A museum staff member, who may have a coaching relationship with another employee.
- **Coach Relationship**: A one-to-many relationship where a senior employee coaches junior employees.

